It was the beginning of the season, I was one week away from a snowboarding trip to the midwest, and I had broken my wrist on my brand new snowboard. Recovery wasn't easy, I ended up having surgery after the natural healing turned out to be maligned, I missed the trip, missed the mountains, and sat in my apartment while my housemate Barker enjoyed the holiday we were meant to be having together.

I was never annoyed with snowboarding for the damage I had cauased myself, I knew that it was a result of many factors that someone with more experience and patience would have avoided. I worked hard at my physiotherapy and took solice in repeatadly watching episodes of Adventure Time and The Art of Flight.

