Finally it was the winter of 2013 and I was able to snowboard again, it had been years since I had boarded with Nixon and Jones, so I took the opportunity to head back out to Japan. This time instead of headed to the touristy location of Hakuba we were visiting a small town of Myoko that the boys had been to the year before.

I was nervous, I was making a lot of mistakes and repeating a lot of bad habits, as such I took it pretty easy. Ultimately I had a great time, and once again the guys were able to give me some tips on how I could improve, I knew that I wanted to keep snowboarding.

Early 2014 I took my first trip to Breckenridge Colorado, thanks to legalization I was able to combine my love for the mountains with my enjoyment of smoking trees. I had discovered a completely different approach to a sport I had once loved, but now was also slightly nervous of. I was able to numb my anxieties and overthinking, and instead just enjoy gliding down the mountain with my mates.

Stoned-boarding would become a big part of how I took on the mountains in 2015, I wasn't able to develop new techniques this way, but I was able to get rid of my bad habits and focus on enjoying myself. I visited Colorado and Canada on numerous occasions, I'd found my rhythm again, even if it was with the help of a substance.

